    {
      "textBlocks": [
        {
          "body": "The wereboar can use its action to polymorph into a boar-humanoid hybrid or into a boar, or back into its true form, which is humanoid. Its statistics, other than its AC, are the same in each form. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying isn't transformed. It reverts to its true form if it dies.",
          "title": "Shapechanger"
        },
        {
          "body": "If the wereboar takes 14 damage or less that would reduce it to 0 hit points, it is reduced to 1 hit point instead.",
          "title": "Relentless (Recharges after a Short or Long Rest)"
        },
        {
          "body": "The wereboar makes two attacks, only one of which can be with its tusks.",
          "title": "Multiattack"
        },
        {
          "body": "The statistics presented in this section assume a base creature of human. However, you can also use the statistics to represent nonhuman lycanthropes, adding verisimilitude by allowing a nonhuman lycanthrope to retain one or more of its humanoid racial traits. For example, an elf werewolf might have the Fey Ancestry trait.",
          "title": "Variant: Nonhuman Lycanthropes"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Abilities"
